# TARA environment variables.
# Copy to .env.local and fill in.
#
# Everything below CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT/NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL is a *Convex*
# environment variable, not a Next.js one — set those with
# `npx convex env set NAME value`, not in this file. They're listed here
# only so you have one place that documents every secret the app needs.
# See docs/SECURITY.md for the full go-live checklist.

# Convex deployment backing the catalogue, orders, auth, and verifications.
# Run `npx convex dev` once to generate these for your own deployment, or
# copy them from an existing one.
CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT=
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=

# ── Convex Auth (set via `npx @convex-dev/auth` / `npx convex env set`) ────
# SITE_URL             — this app's public origin, e.g. https://tarapeptides.com
#                         (also used as the SumUp redirect_url base)
# JWT_PRIVATE_KEY, JWKS — generated by the Convex Auth CLI setup, not hand-written
# AUTH_GOOGLE_ID        — Google OAuth client id (console.cloud.google.com)
# AUTH_GOOGLE_SECRET    — Google OAuth client secret
# AUTH_RESEND_KEY       — Resend API key, used for sign-up/reset verification codes
# AUTH_EMAIL_FROM       — verified sender, e.g. "TARA Peptides <verify@tarapeptides.com>"

# ── SumUp (see convex/SUMUP.md) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# SUMUP_SECRET_KEY      — server-side only, never exposed to the client
# SUMUP_MERCHANT_CODE   — your SumUp merchant code

# ── Resend (see convex/RESEND.md) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# RESEND_API_KEY        — used for order-confirmation emails
# RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET — signing secret for the /resend/webhook endpoint (whsec_...)
